Nova donor bundle for {{.Name}} (Nebula overlay IP {{.NebulaIP}})
================================================================

TWO trust roots — keep them straight:
  Nebula overlay (mesh membership):   nebula-ca.crt / nebula.crt / nebula.key
  Nova federation HTTP mTLS (app id): federation-ca.crt / federation.crt / federation.key

1. Nebula certs (run on the operator host that holds the Nebula CA — NOT novactl):
     nebula-cert ca   -name "Nova Overlay CA"             # once, if you have no CA yet
     nebula-cert sign -name "{{.Name}}" -ip "{{.NebulaIP}}" \
                      -ca-crt nebula-ca.crt -ca-key nebula-ca.key
   Copy nebula-ca.crt, nebula.crt, nebula.key into this bundle.

2. Federation certs (already issued by `novactl node issue`):
     federation-ca.crt, federation.crt, federation.key

3. Hand the bundle to the donor. They run:
     docker compose up -d
   nova-node binds only the Nebula interface; it publishes no ports.

Lighthouse: {{.LighthouseOverlayIP}} (public {{.LighthousePublicIP}}).
Coordinator federation endpoint: https://{{.CoordinatorOverlayIP}}:9443
